                     </origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Within the initial O <locus from="1ra" to="1ra">(fol. 1<hi
                           rend="superscript">ra</hi>)</locus>, a blazon, argent (?), a barry of
                     three, or, on the top argent bar ‘I’affie bien’ and on the second ‘leynthale’
                     plus a mark. Similarly, in the lower margin, <locus from="50ra" to="50ra">fol.
                           50<hi rend="superscript">ra</hi></locus>, ‘I’affie bien LEYNTHALE’ plus
                     mark <date calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="1475" notAfter="1500">(s. xv
                        ex.)</date>. Apparently to be associated with the arms of <persName
                        key="person_4618" role="fmo">Sir Rowland Leynthall</persName> of <placeName
                        key="">Leynthall</placeName> and <placeName key="">Hampton Court
                        (Herefordshire)</placeName> , who fought at <placeName key=""
                        >Agincourt</placeName>, but these bear no resemblance to the modern
                     derivatives.</provenance>
                  <provenance>Pen-trials <date calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="1475" notAfter="1500"
                        >(s. xv ex.)</date> and <locus from="134v" to="134v">(fol. 134<hi
                           rend="superscript">v</hi>).</locus></provenance>
               </history>
